    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Clay</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 63.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg, Russia,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 22, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch No. 683 (circular) is
                            received, for which I thank you. I have this morning telegraphic news of
                            the re-election of A. Lincoln as President. I feel that our country is
                            now secure of the future; that slavery will be abolished, the Union
                            restored, and that we will henceforth take our true position in the
                            world as the leaders in all liberalism in fact, as we have heretofore
                            been in theory. * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C. M. CLAY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon, <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
